.TH "HTMLMetaElement.media" "JS" "July 5, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLMetaElement.media \- HTMLMetaElement: media property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]HTMLMetaElement.media\f[B]\f[R] property enables
specifying the media for \f[CR]theme\-color\f[R] metadata.
.PP
The \f[CR]theme\-color\f[R] property enables setting the color of the
browser\[cq]s toolbar or UI in browsers and operating systems that
support this property.
The \f[CR]media\f[R] property enables setting different theme colors for
different \f[CR]media\f[R] values.
.SH VALUE
A string.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Setting the theme color for dark mode
The following example creates a new \f[CR]<meta>\f[R] element with a
\f[CR]name\f[R] attribute set to \f[CR]theme\-color\f[R].
The \f[CR]content\f[R] attribute is set to \f[CR]#3c790a\f[R], the
\f[CR]media\f[R] attribute is set to
\f[CR]prefers\-color\-scheme: dark\f[R], and the element is appended to
the document \f[CR]<head>\f[R].
When a user has specified a dark mode in their operating system, the
\f[CR]media\f[R] property can be used to set a different
\f[CR]theme\-color\f[R]:
.IP
.EX
var meta = document.createElement(\[dq]meta\[dq]);
meta.name = \[dq]theme\-color\[dq];
meta.content = \[dq]#3c790a\[dq];
meta.media = \[dq](prefers\-color\-scheme: dark)\[dq];
document.head.appendChild(meta);
.EE
.SS Setting theme colors by device size
Most meta properties can be used only once.
However, \f[CR]theme\-color\f[R] can be used multiple times if unique
\f[CR]media\f[R] values are provided.
.PP
This example adds two meta elements with a \f[CR]theme\-color\f[R]; one
for all devices and another for small screens.
The order of matching the \f[CR]media\f[R] query matters, so the more
specific query should be added later in the document, as shown below:
.IP
.EX
// Add a theme\-color for all devices
meta = document.createElement(\[dq]meta\[dq]);
meta.name = \[dq]theme\-color\[dq];
meta.content = \[dq]#ffffff\[dq];
document.head.appendChild(meta);

// Add a theme\-color for small devices
var meta = document.createElement(\[dq]meta\[dq]);
meta.name = \[dq]theme\-color\[dq];
meta.media = \[dq](max\-width: 600px)\[dq];
meta.content = \[dq]#000000\[dq];
document.head.appendChild(meta);
.EE
